# Testing Flow

- Mirror `src/cinemind/` structure in `tests/unit/` when adding or moving backend modules.
- Prefer deterministic tests using fakes or mocks; never depend on live network or API keys.
- Name tests by behavior (`test_<behavior>`) and keep assertions focused on user-visible outcomes.
- For integration helpers, include happy-path, no-credentials, and provider-failure contract cases.
- If request routing, prompting, or extraction behavior changes, update scenario coverage as needed.
- Keep tests fast and isolated; use fixtures to avoid shared mutable state between test functions.
